## Features

### Core Functionality

- Create new campus events
- Edit existing events
- Delete events with confirmation
- Persistent storage using localStorage
- Auto-saving of all changes
- Import and export data using JSON files

### Event Fields

Each event contains:
- Unique ID
- Event name
- Due date
- Duration
- Tag
- Created timestamp
- Updated timestamp

---

## Regex Validation

The application uses regular expressions to validate all user inputs.

### Event Name Validation

- No leading or trailing spaces
- No multiple spaces
- No duplicate words

Pattern:
^\S(?:.*\S)?$
\b(\w+)\s+\1\b

---

### Due Date Validation

Ensures correct format YYYY-MM-DD and valid ranges.

Pattern:
^\d{4}-(0[1-9]|1[0-2])-(0[1-9]|[12]\d|3[01])$

---

### Duration Validation

Allows only numeric values with up to two decimal places.

Pattern:
^(0|[1-9]\d*)(\.\d{1,2})?$

---

### Tag Validation

Allows only letters, spaces, and hyphens.

Pattern:
^[A-Za-z]+(?:[ -][A-Za-z]+)*$

---

## Advanced Regex Feature

The application includes an advanced regex feature to detect duplicate words using back-references:

\b(\w+)\s+\1\b

This helps prevent invalid repeated input such as "Gym Gym".

---

## Search Functionality

- Supports live regex-based search
- Case-insensitive matching
- Safe regex compilation using try/catch
- Fallback to normal text search when regex is invalid
- Filters by event name and tag
- Displays highlighted matches using <mark>

---

## Data Storage

- Uses browser localStorage
- Data automatically persists after every change
- No backend required

Storage Key:
records

---

## Import and Export

### Export
- Downloads all records as a JSON file
- File name: campus-data.json

### Import
- Accepts JSON file upload
- Validates that data is an array
- Safely loads records into the application

---

## Sorting Features

Users can sort records by:
- Event name (A–Z)
- Due date (ascending)
- Duration (numeric ascending)

---

## Dashboard Features

The dashboard displays:

- Total number of events
- Total duration (converted to selected unit)
- Most frequent tag
- Weekly distribution chart (based on due date)

---

## Units System

Supports duration display in:
- Minutes
- Hours (converted from minutes)

---

## Accessibility

The project includes accessibility improvements:

- Semantic HTML structure (header, nav, main, section, footer)
- ARIA live region for status messages
- Keyboard-friendly form controls
- Visible focus indicators
- Proper label associations for inputs

---

## Keyboard Support

- Navigation through sections using menu links
- Form submission using Enter key
- Button-based actions for edit and delete

---

## Testing

A custom test suite is included in tests.html.

It verifies:
- Regex validation rules
- Advanced duplicate word detection
- Search filtering logic
- Error handling for invalid inputs

To run tests:
Open tests.html in a browser.

